quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  26,123,Ad denied the ones who are sent
  26,124,"when their brother Hud said to them: Will you not be Godfearing"
  26,125,"Truly, I am a trustworthy Messenger to you"
  26,126,so be Godfearing of God and obey me
  26,127,And I ask you not for any compensation for it. My compensation is only from the Lord of the worlds
  26,128,Build you a sign on every high hill to amuse
  26,129,And take you for yourselves castles so that perhaps you will dwell in them forever
  26,130,"And when you seized by force, seized you by force haughtily"
  26,131,So be Godfearing of God and obey me
  26,132,Be Godfearing of Him Who furnished relief to you with all that you know
  26,133,He furnished relief to you with flocks and children
  26,134,and gardens and springs
  26,135,"Truly, I fear for you the punishment of a tremendous Day"
  26,136,"They said: It is equal to us whether thou wert to admonish or thou hast not been among the ones who admonish"
  26,137,"Truly, this is nothing but morals of the ancient ones"
  26,138,and we are not ones who are punished
  26,139,"So they denied him and We caused them to perish. Truly, in this is a sign yet most of them had not been ones who believe"
  26,140,"And, truly, thy Lord, He is, certainly, The Almighty, The Compassionate"